title: fuzzywuzzy
text:
Common Errors Included…

East Charter HS vs. East Charter High School
Overton Academy vs. Overton
Jackson High School vs. Robert Jackson High School
and many more combinations and possible errors

title: fuzzywuzzy
text:
Solution: fuzzywuzzy Python package!

pip install fuzzywuzzy
Quantifies the similarity between strings

My approach:

For entries without a clear match, I filtered for the same city and state
Made matches with a fuzz ratio greater than 0.9

title: fuzzywuzzy
text:
fuzzywuzzy Options

Ratio (Simple Ratio) fuzz.ratio("Humpty Dumpty sat on a wall", "Humpty Dumpty Sat on a Wall!") >>> 91
Partial Ratio fuzz.partial_ratio("Humpty Dumpty sat on a wall", "Humpty") >>> 100
Token Set Ratio fuzz.token_set_ratio("Humpty Dumpty sat on a wall", "Humpty Humpty Dumpty sat on a wall") >>> 100
Token Sort Ratio fuzz.token_sort_ratio("Humpty Dumpty sat on a wall","Dumpty Humpty wall on sat a") >>> 100

Source: Jash Data Sciences

title: fuzzywuzzy
text:
Sample Code

!pip install fuzzywuzzy
from fuzzywuzzy import fuzz

# Two strings to compare
str1 = "Humpty"
str2 = "Humpty!"

# Calculate fuzz ratio
simple_ratio = fuzz.ratio(str1, str2)
print(f"The fuzz ratio is {simple_ratio}")
partial_ratio = fuzz.partial_ratio(str1, str2)
print(f"The fuzz partial ratio is {partial_ratio}")
token_set_ratio = fuzz.token_set_ratio(str1, str2)
print(f"The fuzz token set ratio is {token_set_ratio}")
token_sort_ratio = fuzz.token_sort_ratio(str1, str2)
print(f"The fuzz token sort ratio is {token_sort_ratio}")

Requirement already satisfied: fuzzywuzzy in /opt/anaconda3/lib/python3.9/site-packages (0.18.0)

title: About
text:
Welcome to my portfolio! I truly appreciate your page view and interest in my work. My name is Katherine Mead and I am a masters student in Data Science and Analytics at Georgetown University.
I enter the field of data science as a former teacher which informs my approach to human-centered design and research interests.
For general questions and business inquiries, please send me a note at kam515@georgetown.edu.
